PEOPLE WHO DISAGREE WITH THE IDEA ARE JUST ENEMIES OF PROGRESS, SINCE WHEN IS EDUCATION BAD FOR THE COUNTRY?- ANGIE MOTSHEKGA</em>Minister of basic education said she won t be stopped from offering promising youth who are disadvantaged because they don t have matric certificate. Like I said before it will boost the country s literacy rate, it will help more people find employment or tertiary education you name it . Said Angie Motshekga. The minister said the department is busy refining the requirements and selection process to make sure there are no glitches and loopholes.